data.title: Person: Mark Dempsey
data.meta_description: Person: Mark Dempsey: A comprehensive series of articles on this topic
data.text:
Coláiste Choilm Ballincollig 52 Patrician College Newbridge 51: Coláiste Choilm, Ballincollig won the U19A All-Ireland Schools League in dramatic fashion, beating Patrician College Newbridge with the last score of the game at the National Arena.

New Cardiff manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer has summoned the spirit of Alex Ferguson and Roy Keane as he bids to keep the club in the Premier League.

Limerick FC chairman Pat O’Sullivan says the club won’t rush into finding a new manager after the newly-promoted Shannonsiders surprisingly parted company with manager Pat Scully.

A YOUNG man crashed a stolen Honda Civic into a Garda car injuring the driver and then sped off and did not stop until he crashed and wrote off the car.

EXPECTANT mothers can half the chances of undergoing an emergency Caesarean if problems with a baby are first spotted by ultrasound scans during pregnancy.

Cork City take on a Kilkenny City team facing their second game in 48 hours in the eircom League Cup tonight at Turner’s Cross.

The PFAI, the Irish soccer’s players’ union, has voted in a new management committee to see it through to next summer.

WATERFORD UNITED manager, Jimmy McGeough, had no hesitation in admitting that his enthusiastic young squad of players had surprised him by the manner in which they had so quickly settled into the challenge of Premier Division football.

CORK CITY will have to plan without midfielder Conor O’Grady for their remaining two matches in the Eircom league premier division, tonight’s tie against St Patrick’s Athletic and next week’s contest with UCD.

BOHEMIANS manager Stephen Kenny will challenge his team to complete a clean sweep by extending their unbeaten run in the eircom League to nine matches when they play Drogheda United at Dalymount Park tonight.

Premier Division new boys Drogheda enjoyed an opening day win at O2 Park as Derry City went home empty handed.

Mark Dempsey's substitution got Bohemians out of jail for the second week
